HEADWORD: Handwheel
<hw>Hand"wheel`</hw> <pr>(-hw⟦emac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>Any wheel worked by hand; esp., one the rim of
which serves as the handle by which a valve, car brake, or other part is
adjusted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hand-winged</ent>⟦br⟧
